==English==
===Etymology===
First attested from [[w:1515|1515]], from [[Middle English]] [[lode]] ''guide'' + [[stone]], was used as a guide tool by [[mariner]]s. See also: [[lodestar]].

===Noun===
'''loadstone'''
#''Archaic.'' A [[magnet]], iron oxide in the form of [[w:magnetite|magnetite]].
====Synonyms====
*[[lodestone]]
